        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the reference to Kölliker’s visit to Down (see n. 6, below).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2"><hi rend="italic">Virgularia</hi> is a member of the order Pennatulacea, sea pens.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">CD may refer to his zoological notes from the <hi rend="italic">Beagle</hi> voyage; see DAR 30: 106–11 (R. D. Keynes ed. 2000, pp. 96–100).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">CD refers to Karl Gottfried Semper. The notes and specimen have not been identified.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f5">CD discussed <hi rend="italic">Virgularia patagonica</hi> (now considered a ‘nomen nudem’, that is, invalid because the name is based on lost or inadequate specimens) in <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_4252.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Journal of researches</hi> 2d ed.</ref>, pp. 99–100. He refers to Alcide Charles Victor Dessalines d’Orbigny.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f6">Kölliker visited Down on 15 April 1870 (see letters from <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1779.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Albert Günther</ref>, [<hi rend="italic">c.</hi> 9 April 1870] and 12 April 1870).</note>
